 an interview, essays, and critical work on his poetics. Ernesto Livon-Grosman has selected elegant and precise translations by James Irby, G.J. Racz, Nathaniel Tarn, and Roberto Tejada. His insightful introduction places the poet in the wider context of Cuban and Latin American cultural history.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 4aAmerica. 4aLatin America. 4aSpanish literature. 4aliterature. 7aPOETRY / General.2bisacsh  abaroque poetry.  acaribbean.  acontemporary poetry.  acontinental america.  acuba.  acuban literature.  acuban poetry.  aenglish translations.  aindigenous culture.  aindigenous.  ajose lezama lima.  aland rights.  alatin america.  alatin american literature.  alatin american poetry.  aliterature.  amodern poetry.  aneo baroque.  anestor perlongher.  aparadiso.  apoetics.  apoetry translations.  apoetry.  asevero sarduy.  aspanish.  atransnational.  awork dliterature.1 aAlvarez Bravo, Armando, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCortázar, Julio, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLezama Lima, José, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLivon-Grosman, Ernesto, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLivon-Grosman, Ernesto, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSurdity, Severo, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052023476540uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/9780520936553?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520936553423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520936553/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  Univer